                  <Text layoutX="62.0" layoutY="323.0" strokeType="OUTSIDE" strokeWidth="0.0" text="The if statement is one of the simplest ways to control program flow. It evaluates a condition and executes a block of code only if the condition is true. The else statement can be added to execute code when the condition is false. Additionally, else if allows for multiple conditions to be tested in sequence, enabling more complex decision trees within a program." textAlignment="JUSTIFY" wrappingWidth="727.7760620117188">
