                  <Text layoutX="62.0" layoutY="752.0" strokeType="OUTSIDE" strokeWidth="0.0" text="C allows if statements to be nested inside each other, meaning you can place one if or if-else block inside another. While nesting provides flexibility, it can also lead to reduced readability if not used carefully. Logical operators like &amp;&amp; (AND), || (OR), and ! (NOT) are often used to combine or modify conditions, giving programmers greater control over decision-making logic." textAlignment="JUSTIFY" wrappingWidth="727.7760620117188">
